  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      An end-tidal CO 2 monitor (capnometer) is used most often as a noninvasive substitute for
      PaCO2 in anesthesia, anesthetic recovery and intensive care. There is now also wide-spread
      use of capnometry on-site at emergency and trauma fields. So, portable device can be used
      usefully.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
